DEVELOPMENT LICENCE SIGNING KEY — NOT A SECRET, NOT FOR PRODUCTION.

This is the private half of DEV_LICENCE_PUBLIC_KEY in apps/api/src/licence/licence-key.ts. It is
committed on purpose so a fresh checkout can mint a licence and the E2E suite can run, exactly
like the deterministic dev key in apps/api/src/common/crypto.ts.

Because it is public, any licence it signs is forgeable. licencePublicKey() therefore refuses the
matching public key when NODE_ENV=production: a real deployment sets LICENCE_PUBLIC_KEY to the
vendor's own key, generated once with

  node ops/licence/mint-licence.mjs --new-key

and kept off every machine but the vendor's.

